Kaduna State Government has announced Sunday 16th and Monday, 17th August 2020, as resumption dates for Senior Secondary School students (SS3). It also provided the latest update on resumptions and examinations for the rest of the classes, including the SS1, SS2 and JSS1-2, as well as primary schools. The State’s Ministry of Education disclosed this in a statement via its official website on Friday. It also directed administrators of public and private schools to make necessary preparations to accommodate the JSS3 students in line with the COVID-19 guidelines, as it were in the case of the SS3. It said: “The @GovKaduna has approved Sunday 16th and Monday, 17th August 2020, as the resumption dates for the Junior Secondary School (JSS)3 students that are expected to begin their Basic Education Certificate Examination (BECE) slated for 24th August 2020.” “The appropriate resumptions dates for other examinations and the rest of the classes, including the SS1, SS2 and JSS1-2, as well as primary schools, will be announced in due course.”  <img class="aligncenter wp-image-828876 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kaduna-727x1024.jpg" alt="" width="727" height="1024" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kaduna-727x1024.jpg 727w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kaduna-213x300.jpg 213w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kaduna-1091x1536.jpg 1091w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kaduna.jpg 1454w" sizes="(max-width: 727px) 100vw, 727px">